reviewText: Rented this from Redbox, needed some low key family entertainment after all the intense stuff out there.  This is a ABC Family Movie, and it stays true to it's format, mild drama, silly humor, nice people.The gazillionaire owner of a solar/green energy company takes his family, 2 grown up children from prior, widowed marriage, and baby and wife from new marriage(see parts I & II, if you can find them!) to gorgeous Puerto Rico for family time together.Of course, it's hard to get everyone on the same page in paradise: there's some mild thematic tension between what father wants and what his young, adult children seek in life; what wife wants- more babies, stay at home?, and the fact that his company is in trouble.The same main actors reprise their roles.  Gregory Harrison has aged nicely since I remember him in "Trapper John, M.D.".  Hard to believe he'll hit 60 this year- what a great smile!The acting, editing, music are adequate, nothing memorable or emotionally stirring. The locations are great.  If you like TV family shows or Hallmark, you'll like this one.  If not, skip it.  3-1/2*.
